----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
Why you'll never have to dial a phone number again. 



***************************************************************************** 
Tips & Tricks 
***************************************************************************** 
You already know that To Do lets you keep track of 
those little tasks that call upon you each day. 
But did you also know that you can add even 
greater detail or organize them into different 
categories? If you didn't, you're about to find out 
how. 


----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
Adding Details to To Do's 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
Once you've created a To Do item, you can still 
add more details if you need them. Tap anywhere 
on the original To Do and then tap Details at 
the bottom of the screen to bring up the To Do Item 
Details. From there you can enter its priority, 
category (see below) and due date. Then if you tap 
Note, you can enter more details, like driving 
directions and instructions. 

If you liked this tip, you can let us know by 
clicking below:
http://mojofarm.mediaplex.com/ad/ck/629-4408-2493-28?ck=tip&1


----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
Creating To Do Categories 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
Always have a ton of tasks on your plate? Keep your 
To Do items organized in separate categories. To 
create a category, tap the right corner pull-down 
menu and select Edit Categories. Tap New and enter 
the name of the category (work, evening, groceries, 
etc.). Then when you create a new To Do item, tap 
Details and select the category of your choice. 

If you liked this tip, you can let us know by 
clicking below:
http://mojofarm.mediaplex.com/ad/ck/629-4408-2493-28?ck=tip&2



