Write Stuff 
***************************************************************************** 
The holidays are just around the corner, and toy 
stores around the country are gearing up. Just ask 
Visor handheld owners Kevin and Cindy of Wisconsin. 


----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
Designing the Perfect Toy Store 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
My wife and I both have Visor handhelds. She has 
the basic and I have the Deluxe. We both have the 
eyemodule1 and the VisorPhone. 

My wife is an area manager for a large toy company. 
She is based in Wisconsin and her territory includes 
Wisconsin, Illinois, and Minnesota. She uses the 
eyemodule1 to immediately capture visual examples 
of how stores in her territory should be set up and 
sends them (via the VisorPhone) to her headquarters 
in live time. For example, her bosses were planning 
a presentation and asked that she take a picture of 
a merchandiser and send it. The photo was taken in 
Illinois at about 10:30 a.m., and her corporate 
headquarters in Rhode Island had it by 11:00 a.m. 

When my wife had to be out of town on a business 
trip during our daughter's graduation from fifth 
grade, I was able to take pictures of our 
daughter's graduation and email them to my wife 
within twenty minutes of the ceremony. As you 
can see, with the addition of the modules we 
have purchased, our Visor handhelds have allowed 
us to better organize our busy lives. 



