<font face="Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif" size="2">You already know that To Do lets you keep track of 
those little tasks that call upon you each day. But did you also know that you can add even greater 
detail or organize them into different categories? If you didn't, you're about to find out how.<br>
<br><font face="Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif" size="3"><b>Adding Details to To Do's</b></font><br>
Once you've created a To Do item, you can still add more details if you need them. Tap anywhere on the original To Do and then tap Details at the bottom of the screen to bring up the To Do Item Details. From there you can enter its priority, category (see below) and due date. Then if you tap Note, you can enter more details, like driving directions and instructions.
<br>If you liked this tip, you can let us know by <a href="http://4at3.net/KC15271645.4131.0.4624">clicking here</a>.
<br><br>
<font face="Arial, Helvetica, Sans-Serif" size="3"><b>Creating To Do Categories</b></font><br>
Always have a ton of tasks on your plate? Keep your To Do items organized in separate categories. 
To create a category, tap the right corner pull-down menu and select Edit Categories. Tap New and 
enter the name of the category (work, evening, groceries, etc.). Then when you create a new To Do 
item, tap Details and select the category of your choice.<br>
If you liked this tip, you can let us know by <a href="http://4at3.net/KC15271645.4131.0.4625">clicking here</a>.<br>
